OL,7,FMrs Scaldwell said in her statement
OL,8,Fthat was read to court that she has to
OL,9,Fsleep downstairs in the dining room as
OL,10,Fshe cannot climb stairs.
OL,12,FShe has limited use of her hands and
OL,13,Fstruggles to eat as she lost her teeth
OL,14,Fin the collision and cannot hold a
OL,15,Fknife and fork.
OL,17,FThe court heard she has been left with
OL,18,F"multiple life changing injuries"
OL,19,Fwhich means she has no social life or
OL,20,Fconfidence and is on anti-depressants,
OL,21,Fshe cannot leave the house on her own.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/12
