OL,4,Cpensioner hit by e-bike still in
OL,5,Cconstant pain
OL,7,FJoel Pilling had bought the Talaria
OL,8,FSting e-bike from a friend for #3,200.
OL,9,FIt was not taxed or insured and the
OL,10,Fbreaks were faulty.
OL,12,FJudge Jon Close said that even if the
OL,13,Fbreaks were in working order it could
OL,14,Fnot have stopped in time when it was
OL,15,Ftravelling at least 10 mph over the
OL,16,Fspeed limit. The e-bike was made even
OL,17,Fmore unsteady as it was carrying a
OL,18,Fpassenger at the time.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/12
