OL,7,FHe was given a 22 months jail sentence
OL,8,Fsuspended for two years plus 250 hours
OL,9,Funpaid work. He was also disqualified
OL,10,Ffrom driving for two years .
OL,12,FMrs Scaldwell has now called on the
OL,13,FGovernment to do more to tackle the
OL,14,Fnumber of modified or high-powered e-
OL,15,Fbikes and e-scooters ridden on roads
OL,16,Fand pavements which put vulnerable
OL,17,Fpedestrians at risk.
